(46, 'Beginning Physics II - (Waves, Electromagnetism, Optics and Modern Physics)', 'Alvin Halpern, ErichErlbach', 'Introductory Physics III', 'textbook', 'fig,magnetic,chap,circuit,voltage,emf,flux,magnetic field, Heat and Thermodynamics,Sound Waves, Electrostatics, Current Electricity and Magnetism, Ray Optics and Wave Optics, Modern Physics, capacitor, coil, calculate, wire, magnitude, ans, frequency, axis, radius, cos, induced, velocity, cord, resistor,inductance,perpendicular,solenoid,sphere,inductor,equals,wavelength,voltage across,refraction,capacitance,conductor,circuits,molecules,battery, electromagnetic, flows, amplitude, conducting, currents, incidence, propagation,loop, vector, toroid, cylinder, 1induced emf, density, travelling, magnetism, displacement, torque, wires, shown in fig,electric circuits,formula,transverse,magnet,equation', 'Okeke Johnpaul', 'img46.png', '', '', '2011', '545', 1, 27),
(47, 'Organic Chemistry - Schaum\'s Outline', 'Herbert Meislich ', 'Introductory Chemistry II', 'textbook', 'Structure and Properties of Organic Compounds, Bonding and Molecular Structure ,Chemical Reactivity and Organic Reactions, Alkanes , Stereochemistry , Alkenes,  Alkyl Halides, Alkynes and Dienes , Cyclic Hydrocarbons,  Benzene and Polynuclear Aromatic Compounds , Aromatic Substitution; Arenes , Spectroscopy and Structure, Alcohols and Thiols , Ethers, Epoxides, Glycols, and Thioethers, Carbonyl Compounds: Aldehydes and Ketones , Carboxylic Acids and their Derivatives ,Carbanion-Enolates and Enols,  Amines , Phenolic Compounds, Aromatic Heterocyclic Compounds', 'Okeke Johnpaul', 'img47.png', '', 'The beginning student in Organic Chemistry is often overwhelmed by facts, concepts, and new language. Each year, textbooks of Organic Chemistry grow in quantity of subject matter and in level of sophistication. This Schaum’s Outline was undertaken to give a clear view of first-year Organic Chemistry through the careful detailed solution of illustrative problems. Such problems make up over 80% of the book, the remainder being a concise presentation of the material. Our goal is for students to learn by thinking and solving problems rather than by merely being told.', '2011', '481', 1, 13),
(48, 'Theory and Problems of Optics - Schaums', 'Eugene Hecht', 'Introductory Physics II', 'textbook', 'plane,lens,diffraction,optical,function,cos4,phase,waves,aperture,intensity,sin,axis,polarization,frequency,distribution,medium,coherence,fourier,interference,spatial,hologram,principal angle, optics, fields, focal, fringes, amplitude, index, plate, nonlinear, monochromatic, grating, frequencies, eqs, ray,matrix,refraction,polarized,fourier transform,observation,optical system,zero,respectively,light waves, spectral', 'Okeke Johnpaul', 'img48.png', '', '', '2011', '247', 3, 10);
